== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Middle English < Old English '''[[Þurresdæg]]''', a contraction of '''Þunresdæg''' ("[[Thor]]’s [[day]]") < Proto-Germanic '''*thonaras daga-''' < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*(s)tene-]]''' ("to thunder"). See [[day]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-Thursday.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''Thursday'''
#The fourth day of the week in Europe and in systems using the ISO 8601 norm.
#:It follows [[Wednesday]] and precedes [[Friday]].
#The fifth [[day]] of the [[week]] in the USA.
#An appointment, person, or feeling associated with this day of the week.

